OF THE BOSCA.

The Bosca is a water sowl, like to a Duck¹, but smaller. Since there are many water fowls like to the Duck‚ but smaller (as there surely are), called Teles, Wigenes and Pochards by the English, Ι believe the Bosca to be that which comes nearest the size and likeness of a Duck. And since the Pochard does so, Ι decide that it is Aristotle's Bosca.
